## GraphQL Integration

### Craft CMS GraphQL Setup
1. Enable GraphQL in Craft CMS: Settings > GraphQL
2. Create a schema with appropriate scope
3. Generate an API token for the frontend

### Data Fetching in Nuxt

```typescript
// composables/useCraft.ts
export const useCraftQuery = async <T>(query: string, variables?: Record<string, any>) => {
  const config = useRuntimeConfig();

  return useFetch<T>(config.public.craftGraphqlUrl, {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: {
      'Content-Type': 'application/json',
      'Authorization': `Bearer ${config.craftGraphqlToken}`,
    },
    body: { query, variables },
  });
};
```

### Example Queries

```graphql
# Fetch entries
query GetBlogPosts($limit: Int) {
  entries(section: "blog", limit: $limit, orderBy: "postDate DESC") {
    id
    title
    slug
    postDate
    url
    ... on blog_blog_Entry {
      summary
      featuredImage {
        url @transform(width: 800, height: 450, mode: "crop")
        alt
      }
    }
  }
}

# Single entry
query GetPage($slug: [String]) {
  entry(section: "pages", slug: $slug) {
    title
    ... on pages_pages_Entry {
      body
      seoDescription
    }
  }
}
```

### Using in Pages

```vue
<!-- pages/blog/index.vue -->
<script setup lang="ts">
const { data } = await useCraftQuery(`
  query {
    entries(section: "blog", limit: 10, orderBy: "postDate DESC") {
      title
      slug
      postDate
      ... on blog_blog_Entry {
        summary
      }
    }
  }
`);
</script>

<template>
  <div>
    <h1>Blog</h1>
    <article v-for="post in data?.entries" :key="post.slug">
      <NuxtLink :to="`/blog/${post.slug}`">
        <h2>{{ post.title }}</h2>
      </NuxtLink>
      <p>{{ post.summary }}</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</template>
```

## Nuxt Patterns

### File-Based Routing
```
pages/
├── index.vue           # /
├── about.vue           # /about
├── blog/
│   ├── index.vue       # /blog
│   └── [slug].vue      # /blog/:slug
└── [...slug].vue       # Catch-all for CMS pages
```

### Layouts
```vue
<!-- layouts/default.vue -->
<template>
  <div>
    <AppHeader />
    <main>
      <slot />
    </main>
    <AppFooter />
  </div>
</template>
```

### SEO / Head Management
```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
useHead({
  title: entry.title,
  meta: [
    { name: 'description', content: entry.seoDescription },
    { property: 'og:title', content: entry.title },
    { property: 'og:image', content: entry.featuredImage?.[0]?.url },
  ],
});
</script>
```

## Coding Standards

### PHP (Craft CMS)
- Follow PSR-12 coding standards
- Use type hints for parameters and return types
- Use Craft's service pattern for business logic

### Vue / TypeScript (Nuxt)
- Use `<script setup lang="ts">` for all components
- Use Composition API (no Options API)
- Define props with `defineProps<T>()` using TypeScript generics
- Use `defineEmits<T>()` for typed events
- Prefer composables over mixins
- Use `auto-import` (Nuxt auto-imports components, composables, utils)

### CSS
- Use Tailwind utility classes
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Use `@apply` sparingly, prefer utility classes

## Important Notes

1. **Always use `ddev` prefix** for backend CLI commands
2. **Project config**: Changes sync via `config/project/` YAML files
3. **Environment variables**: Backend in `.env`, frontend in `nuxt.config.ts` runtimeConfig
4. **GraphQL schema**: Manage in Craft CMS admin, version via project config
5. **CORS**: Configure in Craft CMS to allow frontend origin
6. **Preview**: Use Craft's live preview with Nuxt preview mode for content editing

